<PLACE><ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX></PLACE>
<SBODY>▓▓▓▓▓ ---\+ 5 7 0
WARRANTY <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Second__ day of February in the Year
of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and Eighty Seven</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry C Scott</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bethial C
Scott</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Lyndon</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">N. D</ENAMEX>
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Solmon Nottingham</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Elmora</ENAMEX> Wallingham <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> of the same place
of the second part,
Witnesseth, That the said parties of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">thirty five hundred Dollars $3500</NUMEX>=
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Delluse</ENAMEX>,
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> duly paid, have sold, and by these presents do grant and convey to the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,
ALL THAT <ENAMEX TYPE="VEHICLE">TRACTOR</ENAMEX> PARCEL OF LAND, situate in the ⌨own of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Lyndon County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>
being the west part of Lot nine Township four Range <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">three</NUMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Holland Land</ENAMEX>
Companys land bounded west by Lot <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">17 sixty two</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twenty</NUMEX> links north by Lot
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">10 twelve</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Eight</NUMEX> links East by a line parallel to the first mentioned boundary <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">sixty
two</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">six</NUMEX> links and south by Township 3 Range <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">3 twelve</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Eight</NUMEX> links containing
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Seventy five</NUMEX> acres more or less. Also a certain other piece of land situate in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Town of
Ischua</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">County & State aforesaid</ENAMEX> being the North west part of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Lot sixteen Township</ENAMEX> three
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Range three</ENAMEX> bounded west by the west line of said Lot <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ten</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">five</NUMEX> links north by the
north line of Township <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">three fourteen</NUMEX> Chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ninety two</NUMEX> links East by a line parallel to
the west bounds of said Lot <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ten</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">five</NUMEX> links and south by a line parallel to the North
bounds thereof containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifteen</NUMEX> acres more or less, being the North half of premises conveyed by
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Joseph Lockwood</ENAMEX> & <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William H Sinfield</ENAMEX> by deed dated <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">October 18th 1852</TIMEX> Both of said above
described pieces being same premises conveyed to the parties of the first part by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">John O Badger</ENAMEX>
and others by deed dated <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">February 26" 1880</TIMEX>
With the Napurtenanges, and all the Estate, Title and Interest therein of the said parties of the first part. And the said
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry Scott</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bethial C Scott</ENAMEX> parties of the first part
do hereby covenant and agree to and with the said partilt of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,
that the premises thus conveyed in the quiet and peaceable possession of the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX>
will forever WARRANT AND DEFEND against any person <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">whomsoever</ENAMEX> lawfully claiming the same or any part thereof
In Witness Whereof, The parties of the first part have hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> hands and seals the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry Scott</ENAMEX>
[ L. S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Beteare C Scott</ENAMEX> ---\+
[ L. S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">CATERASSUS</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Allgany</ENAMEX> ⎬ On this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">2"
day of February in the year one thousand eight hundred and
Eighty Seven</TIMEX> before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, the subscriber, personally appeared <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry Scott</ENAMEX> & <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bethial C Scott</ENAMEX>
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> personally known to be the same persons described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within
instrument, and severally acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> executed the same.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">J. C. Leggett</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Notary Public</ENAMEX> ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+
hands, and an and belo 3rd
any of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">February__1887</TIMEX>
= ---\+
</SBODY>
</NBX>

WARRANTY <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">Second__ day of February in the Year
of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and Eighty Seven</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry C Scott</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bethial C
Scott</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Lyndon</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">N. D</ENAMEX>
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Solmon Nottingham</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Elmora</ENAMEX> Wallingham <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> of the same place
of the second part,
Witnesseth, That the said parties of the first part, in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">thirty five hundred Dollars $3500</NUMEX>=
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Delluse</ENAMEX>,
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">them</ENAMEX> duly paid, have sold, and by these presents do grant and convey to the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,
ALL THAT <ENAMEX TYPE="VEHICLE">TRACTOR</ENAMEX> PARCEL OF LAND, situate in the ⌨own of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Lyndon County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>
being the west part of Lot nine Township four Range <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">three</NUMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Holland Land</ENAMEX>
Companys land bounded west by Lot <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">17 sixty two</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">twenty</NUMEX> links north by Lot
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">10 twelve</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Eight</NUMEX> links East by a line parallel to the first mentioned boundary <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">sixty
two</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">six</NUMEX> links and south by Township 3 Range <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">3 twelve</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Eight</NUMEX> links containing
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">Seventy five</NUMEX> acres more or less. Also a certain other piece of land situate in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Town of
Ischua</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">County & State aforesaid</ENAMEX> being the North west part of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Lot sixteen Township</ENAMEX> three
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Range three</ENAMEX> bounded west by the west line of said Lot <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ten</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">five</NUMEX> links north by the
north line of Township <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">three fourteen</NUMEX> Chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ninety two</NUMEX> links East by a line parallel to
the west bounds of said Lot <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">ten</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">five</NUMEX> links and south by a line parallel to the North
bounds thereof containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifteen</NUMEX> acres more or less, being the North half of premises conveyed by
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Joseph Lockwood</ENAMEX> & <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX> to <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William H Sinfield</ENAMEX> by deed dated <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">October 18th 1852</TIMEX> Both of said above
described pieces being same premises conveyed to the parties of the first part by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">John O Badger</ENAMEX>
and others by deed dated <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">February 26" 1880</TIMEX>
With the Napurtenanges, and all the Estate, Title and Interest therein of the said parties of the first part. And the said
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry Scott</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bethial C Scott</ENAMEX> parties of the first part
do hereby covenant and agree to and with the said partilt of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>,
that the premises thus conveyed in the quiet and peaceable possession of the said parties of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX>
will forever WARRANT AND DEFEND against any person <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">whomsoever</ENAMEX> lawfully claiming the same or any part thereof
In Witness Whereof, The parties of the first part have hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> hands and seals the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry Scott</ENAMEX>
[ L. S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Beteare C Scott</ENAMEX> ---\+
[ L. S.]
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">CATERASSUS</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Allgany</ENAMEX> ⎬ On this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">2"
day of February in the year one thousand eight hundred and
Eighty Seven</TIMEX> before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, the subscriber, personally appeared <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Henry Scott</ENAMEX> & <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Bethial C Scott</ENAMEX>
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> personally known to be the same persons described in and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the within
instrument, and severally acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> executed the same.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">J. C. Leggett</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Notary Public</ENAMEX> ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+ ---\+

any of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">February__1887</TIMEX>
